properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 10:17AM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED ON SUNDAY...

.A low pressure system will track from the central Plains toward
southern Wisconsin on Sunday. Snow will spread across the area
from southwest to northeast during the morning, continue through
afternoon, and then end during the evening.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches.

* WHERE...Lincoln and Marathon Counties.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Travel could become
dangerous at times.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow is expected to fall from
late morning into early afternoon. Expect snow-covered and
slippery road conditions, along with reduced visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
